Season 22 Election Notes

FORBIDDEN KNOWLEDGE WARNING

This document contains some information that is not currently present on the main site and may be considered spoilers. Continue at your own discretion. Some information in this document cannot be shared on the Discord without spoiler tags.

Last Updated Season 22, Day 97

Decrees

Decrees are chosen by majority votes across all teams. 2 decrees will pass this season.

-Sun

Set Sun. Non-losing with Negative Runs earns you 2 Wins.

See below for the number of additional Wins this would have added. It is unknown how this interacts with the current Turntables/SunSun mess.

Pies would have an extra 0 Wins

Sun 0

Set Sun. Non-losing with Zero Runs earns you 2 Wins.

See below for the number of additional Wins this would have added. It is unknown how this interacts with the current Turntables/SunSun mess.

Pies would have an extra 0 Wins

Equal Sun

Set Sun. A home run during a game's final out ties the game.

This will, presumably, force a game to go into extra innings if the final play is a home run. This will increase the number of Sun 30 Wins awarded.

MAXIMUM SUN

Set Sun. Scoring plays in Maximum Blaseball are worth 3x the Runs.

Maximum Blaseball occurs when all the bases are loaded and there are 2 outs, 2 strikes, and 3 balls in the count. This is a fairly rare occurrence. Note that some players also have Minimalist or Maximalist, making them play better or worse in this situation

Sum Sun

Weather. Each successive scoring play by a Team within a half inning is worth an additional Run.

This weather will reward chaining together many running scores (Whole Team-ing).

Sun 9

Set Sun. Non-losses on the Week End (every 9th Day) are worth 2 Wins.

See below for the number of additional Wins this would have added. It is unknown how this interacts with the current Turntables/SunSun mess.

Pies would have an extra 7 Wins

Wills

Will are selected for each team by raffle. Each team will draw 2 random wills. The bottom 4 teams in the league by standings will draw 3. The chosen wills are random, but wills with more votes are more likely to be selected.

Equivalent Exchange

Swap a Player from a Team in the League with an Equivalent (within 2 Stars) Player on your Team.

See below for the 20 best swap candidates for a particular player, sorted by highest stats in the applicable position.

A random Ego-Boosted Player on your Team gets their Negative Alternate called (maintaining Stars) and they lose 1 Ego.

A Negative Alternate will be a reroll of the player, maintaining Combined Star Count, with eDensity flipped negative. This will also remove 1 Ego level, which will reduce eDensity. Dropping from Ego+ will remove the protection from flooding. See below for list of Ego boosted players.

Combined Batting Pitching Baserunning Defense
